.Dd January 10, 2026
.Dt DOVEGUARD 8
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm doveguard
.Nd Dovecot brute-force blocker for FreeBSD
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl c Ar path
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
monitors Dovecot mail server logs for repeated authentication failures and
blocks abusive IP addresses using PF or IPFW.
It is designed to run as a background service on FreeBSD.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Fl c , Fl Fl config Ar path
Path to configuration file.
If not specified, the default is
.Pa /usr/local/etc/doveguard.conf .
.It Fl h , Fl Fl help
Show help text and exit.
.It Fl V , Fl Fl version
Show version and exit.
.El
.Sh CONFIGURATION
All configuration is read from the file specified with
.Fl c .
The following keys are supported:
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Ic log_path
Path to the mail log to monitor. Default:
.Pa /var/log/maillog .
.It Ic log_output_path
Output log file path. Default:
.Pa /var/log/doveguard/doveguard.log .
.It Ic log_syslog
Enable syslog output (boolean). Default: false.
.It Ic firewall_backend
Firewall backend:
.Ic pf
or
.Ic ipfw .
Default:
.Ic pf .
.It Ic firewall_table
PF table name or IPFW table number. Default:
.Ic doveguard .
.It Ic firewall_runner
Privilege escalation command for firewall calls:
.Ic doas
or
.Ic sudo .
Default: empty (no escalation).
.It Ic window_seconds
Sliding window size for failures in seconds. Default: 600.
.It Ic threshold
Failures before banning. Default: 3.
.It Ic ban_duration_seconds
Ban duration in seconds. Default: 86400.
.It Ic fail_patterns
List of regex patterns (each must include an
.Ic ip
capture group) with descriptions.
.It Ic whitelist
List of CIDR ranges to never ban.
.It Ic dry_run
Log firewall actions without executing them (boolean). Default: false.
.It Ic save_interval_seconds
How often to persist state in seconds. Default: 300.
.It Ic max_log_line_bytes
Maximum log line length in bytes. Default: 65536.
.It Ic max_tracked_ips
Maximum number of IPs to track. Default: 100000.
.It Ic failure_cleanup_interval
Cleanup interval for old failure entries in seconds. Default: 300.
.El
.Sh FIREWALL SETUP
PF example (use a table name that matches
.Ic firewall_table ) :
.Bd -literal -offset indent
table <doveguard> persist counters
block in quick from <doveguard>
.Ed
.Pp
IPFW example (use a table number that matches
.Ic firewall_table ) :
.Bd -literal -offset indent
ipfw table 100 create type addr
ipfw add 1000 deny ip from table(100) to any
.Ed
.Pp
If running as an unprivileged user, set
.Ic firewall_runner
to
.Ic doas
or
.Ic sudo
and allow the required commands (for example,
.Pa /sbin/pfctl
or
.Pa /sbin/ipfw
with table operations).
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Pa /usr/local/etc/doveguard.conf
Configuration file.
.It Pa /usr/local/etc/doveguard.conf.sample
Sample configuration file.
.It Pa /var/db/doveguard/state.json
Persistent ban state.
.It Pa /var/log/doveguard/doveguard.log
Default output log (when file logging is enabled).
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr rc.conf 5 ,
.Xr syslog.conf 5 ,
.Xr pf.conf 5 ,
.Xr pfctl 8 ,
.Xr ipfw 8
